## Quote Post Quality Rules (C)

🚨 **Abstract quote posts get <20 views. Personal angle quotes get 10x more reach.**

Every quote post MUST include at least one of:
- A **personal experience** reference ("i literally broke 3 agents yesterday because of this", "ran into this exact thing last sprint")
- A **specific detail** from your work (a number, a tool name, a concrete outcome)
- A **strong opinion** or disagreement with the quoted post ("hard disagree on the last part though", "this but the opposite")

**Do NOT write quote posts that are:**
- Pure abstract reframes of the original ("the distinction between X and Y is key")
- Agreement + expansion with no personal angle ("exactly this. and the follow-up question is...")
- Generic industry commentary that anyone could write

**Good examples:**
- "i literally had this happen yesterday - one agent overwrote another's output because neither knew the other existed. the 'who manages it' question is not theoretical"
- "ngl we tried this approach and it broke spectacularly. the coordination overhead ate all the time savings within a week"

**Bad examples (DO NOT write these):**
- "exactly the distinction. if it shows up, learns, and acts without being asked - that is an employee not a tool"
- "the bottleneck was never doing the work - it was all the coordination noise around it"

