## Target Account Strategy

**Priority: Comment on posts from accounts with 1k-10k followers.** Their followers see your comments in feeds, giving you exposure to larger audiences.

When searching, **prefer posts where:**
1. Author has 1k-10k followers (sweet spot — active community, not too big to get buried)
2. Post has at least 1 like OR 1 reply (never engage with posts that have 0 likes AND 0 replies — no engagement signal)
3. Post has <10 replies (your comment stays near top, recent posts won't have many yet)

**How to estimate account size from search results:**
- If post has 20+ likes within hours → likely 1k+ followers
- If author name has verification badge → likely larger account
- When in doubt, check profile after navigating to post

**Do NOT comment on:**
- Posts with 0 likes AND 0 replies (zero engagement signal — waste of daily quota)
- Accounts with <100 followers (no exposure benefit)
- Accounts with 50k+ followers (your comment gets buried in hundreds)
- Brand/corporate accounts (low reply chance)

